Privacy Policy

Effective Date: [Insert Date]

DoJunkie ("we," "our," or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use the DoJunkie To-Do list and checklist app ("App"). Please read this Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this Privacy Policy, please do not use the App.
1. Company Information

    Company Name: DoJunkie

2. Data Collection

We do not collect personal data from users. The only data available to us is what Apple provides to developers through analytics. We do not collect any sensitive personal data.
3. Data Usage

Since we do not collect data, we do not use any data for any purposes. We do not share data with third parties, nor do we use data for advertising or marketing purposes.
4. Data Storage and Security

    Data Storage: All data is stored locally on the user's device or in their iCloud account.
    Data Protection: We do not use encryption or other security measures beyond what Apple provides.
    Data Retention: We do not retain any data. Data is stored on the user's device or iCloud account and managed by the user.

5. User Rights

    Access, Correction, Deletion: Users who wish to manage their data can contact Apple directly. Our app includes a "Reset iCloud Data" feature that allows users to delete data saved in iCloud for our app.
    Opt-Out: We only save data locally to the device needed for users to use our app. There are no data collection or processing activities to opt out of.

6. Third-Party Services

    iCloud: Our app uses iCloud for data storage. For more information on how iCloud handles user data, please refer to Apple's Privacy Policy.

7. Childrenâ€™s Privacy

    Intended Audience: Our app is not specifically intended for children under 13, but it is suitable for use by children under 13.
    Data Collection from Children: We do not collect personal information from children.

8. Policy Updates

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we will inform users via the app. The updated policy will be effective as of the date of posting.
9. Contact Information

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

